'''格林布賴爾渡假村'''（The Greenbrier）是位於[[美國|美國]][[西維吉尼亞州|西維吉尼亞州]][[格林布賴爾縣|格林布賴爾郡]][[白硫磺泉镇_(西弗吉尼亚州)|白硫磺泉鎮]]的[[度假旅館|豪華渡假村]]。

該渡假村的歷史可追溯至1778年遊客來此「取水」。當今的渡假村建於1913年。佔地11,000英畝（4,500公頃），擁有710間客房，20個餐廳和會客廳，超過55個室內和室外活動和體育設施以及36個零售商店。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.greenbrier.com/HomePage-Sub-Pages/About-The-Greenbrier |title=About The Greenbrier |access-date=June 9, 2016 |archive-date=2016-06-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160608140744/http://www.greenbrier.com/HomePage-Sub-Pages/About-The-Greenbrier |dead-url=no }}</ref>

格林布賴爾渡假村也是一個大型地下[[地堡|地堡]]的所在地，作為[[冷戰|冷戰]]時[[美國國會|美國國會]]的緊急避難所。<ref name=erglat592>{{cite news |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=4UNWAAAAIBAJ&pg=6422%2C6971259 |newspaper=Eugene Register-Guard |location=Oregon |agency=(Los Angeles Times) |last=Eaton |first=William |title=Congress has a secret bunker under resort |date=May 30, 1992 |page=1A |accessdate=2020-12-08 |archive-date=2021-10-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211014221244/https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=4UNWAAAAIBAJ&pg=6422%2C6971259 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=lnsap92>{{cite news |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=goEzAAAAIBAJ&pg=6906%2C3565588 |newspaper=Lodi News-Sentinel |location=California |agency=Associated Press |title=Congress' secret bunker in hillside by resort |date=May 30, 1992 |page=11}}</ref><ref name=osbkr92>{{cite news |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=oHlIAAAAIBAJ&pg=1829%2C6816659 |newspaper=Ocala Star-Banner |location=Florida |agency=Knight-Ridder Newspapers |last=Webb |first=Tom |title=West Virginia resort harbors nuclear bunker for Congress |date=May 30, 1992 |page=1A}}</ref><ref name=tolbl95>{{cite news |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=VeE0AAAAIBAJ&pg=3920%2C1772670 |newspaper=Toledo Blade |location=Ohio |agency=Associated Press |title=Congress had headquarters for nuclear war |date=November 6, 1995 |page=3}}</ref><ref name=redgap1195>{{cite news |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=jmwlAAAAIBAJ&pg=1228%2C4767739 |newspaper=Reading Eagle |location=Pennsylvania |agency=Associated Press |title=TV viewers get look at secret Congress bunker |date=November 6, 1995 |page=A4}}</ref>

本渡假村的名稱來自[[百合目|百合目]][[菝葜科|菝葜科]]植物[[圓葉菝葜_(北美)|圓葉菝葜]]的別名綠刺藤（Greenbrier），同時也是該郡與郡內主要河流的名稱源。<ref>[https://www.wvencyclopedia.org/articles/42 e-WV | The Greenbrier] {{Wayback|url=https://www.wvencyclopedia.org/articles/42 |date=20201123160535 }}''The name "Greenbrier" (after the county, river, and plant) became the preferred name over the 19th century’s "White Sulphur Springs."''</ref>

